  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A demon lord is a powerful, unique demon that rules a layer of the Abyss. All demon lords are chaotic evil outsiders that are, at a minimum, CR 26. Demon lords have a particular suite of traits (unless otherwise noted in a creature&rsquo;s entry) as summarized here.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"padding-bottom: 1em;\">A demon lord can grant spells to its worshipers as if it were a deity. A demon lord&rsquo;s domains are Chaos, Evil, and two other domains relevant to its theme and interests. Like a deity, a demon lord has a favored weapon.</li>\n<li style=\"padding-bottom: 1em;\">A demon lord&rsquo;s natural weapons, as well as any weapons it wields, are treated as chaotic, epic, and evil for the purpose of overcoming damage reduction.</li>\n<li style=\"padding-bottom: 1em;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf-content.pf-universal-monster-rules\" data-id=\"9U6tgvH9lcoU9Dy7\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">Abyssal Resurrection (Ex)</span></a> A demon lord rules an Abyssal realm, a vast world that not only serves as its home but provides it with power. If a demon lord is slain, its body rapidly melts into corruption (leaving behind any gear it held or carried), its soul returns to a hidden location within its realm, and it is immediately restored to life (as <a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf1.spells\" data-id=\"mxqi375ya2rka7cp\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">true resurrection</span></a>) at that location. Once this occurs, a demon lord can&rsquo;t use this ability again until a full year has passed. A demon lord realizes it is vulnerable during this time and usually doesn&rsquo;t risk further battles for the remainder of that year, relying on the defenses of its realm and its legions of minions to protect it. A demon lord that is slain again during this year or is killed by unusual methods (such as by a true deity or an artifact created for this purpose) is slain forever&mdash;its remains appearing somewhere deep in the Abyss among other dead demon lords from the ages. A demon lord who does not control a domain does not gain this ability.</li>\n<li style=\"padding-bottom: 1em;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf-content.pf-universal-monster-rules\" data-id=\"VwAdaW54wlo1xS63\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">Frightful Presence (Ex)</span></a> A demon lord can activate its frightful presence as a free action as part of any attack, spell-like ability, special attack, or by speaking aloud.</li>\n<li style=\"padding-bottom: 1em;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf-content.pf-universal-monster-rules\" data-id=\"tMXDONflorjcBvOx\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">Immunity</span></a> to ability damage, ability drain, charm effects, compulsion effects, death effects, <a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf-content.pf-universal-monster-rules\" data-id=\"iRhl8Dcw1nH9RAZi\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">energy drain</span></a>, and <a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf1.conditions\" data-id=\"qLQsdbMorUOjOJWJ\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">petrification</span></a>.</li>\n<li style=\"padding-bottom: 1em;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf-content.pf-universal-monster-rules\" data-id=\"LZE96PjxUJxzPVDl\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">Regeneration (Ex)</span></a> Only epic and good damage, or damage from a creature of equal or greater power (such as an archdevil, deity, demon lord, or protean lord) interrupts a demon lord&rsquo;s regeneration.</li>\n<li style=\"padding-bottom: 1em;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf-content.pf-universal-monster-rules\" data-id=\"UmrOVYijTsUxfSqo\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">Resistance</span></a> to acid 30, cold 30, and fire 30.</li>\n<li style=\"padding-bottom: 1em;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf-content.pf-universal-monster-rules\" data-id=\"92KZyngIjPGU6sNQ\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">Summon Demon (Sp)</span></a> Three times per day as a swift action, a demon lord can summon any demon or combination of demons whose total combined CR is 20 or lower. This otherwise works like the <a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf-content.pf-universal-monster-rules\" data-id=\"eJ14u2Ayls8Lt0Af\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">summon</span></a> universal monster rule with a 100% chance of success, and counts as a 9th-level spell effect.</li>\n<li style=\"padding-bottom: 1em;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf-content.pf-universal-monster-rules\" data-id=\"ciDgGX78qznu6wkk\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">Telepathy</span></a>&nbsp;300 feet.</li>\n</ul>",
